text: Faistenau is a municipality in the Austrian state of Salzburg.Faistenau at regionalsuche.at (in German) ==Geography== It is located in the district of Salzburg-Umgebung. It is a significant tourist destination, located in the Salzkammergut region known for its natural lakes. ==Population== As of 15 May 2001 Faistenau had a population of 2,850, of whom 49.6% are male and 50.4% female.Demographic data for Faistenau at Statistik Austria (in German) The earliest population records for Faistenau are from 1869, at which time the municipality had 1,103 inhabitants.Historical data for Faistenau at Statistik Austria (in German) ==References== == External links == * Faistenau municipal council website (in German) * Faistenau at Statistik Austria Category:Cities and towns in Salzburg-Umgebung District
